# StreamHub web — build-time config (Vite). Copy to .env.local and fill in.
#
# The app talks to streamhub-core at /api/v1 (same origin — no build-time config
# needed). The frontend itself requires NO env vars.
#
# Auth is passwordless magic-link:
#   POST /api/v1/auth/magic-link  { email }  → emails a signed sign-in link
#   POST /api/v1/auth/magic/verify { token } → exchanges the link token for a JWT
# The public app lives at https://app.streamhub.studio; the emailed link points
# at https://app.streamhub.studio/auth/magic?token=…
# A break-glass admin form (email/username + password → POST /auth/login) stays
# reachable only via /login?admin=1 for emergencies.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BACKEND (streamhub-core) — NOT read by this Vite app; documented here for ops.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Magic-link emails are sent over SMTP. Configure streamhub-core with:
#   SMTP_HOST=mail.wipermax.online
#   SMTP_PORT=587                       # STARTTLS
#   SMTP_USER=no-reply@streamhub.studio
#   SMTP_FROM="StreamHub <no-reply@streamhub.studio>"
#   SMTP_PASS=__set_via_env_or_secret__ # NEVER hardcode/commit — env or secrets store only
#   SUPERADMIN_EMAIL=info@streamhub.studio
